{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Alice Glacier | other_name = | photo = | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Alice Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = tributary | location = [[East Antarctica]] | coordinates = {{coord|83|58|S|170|0|E|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = {{convert|24|km|mi|abbr=on}} | width = | thickness = | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Beardmore Glacier]] | status = | embedded = }}
'''Alice Glacier''' ({{coord|83|58||S|170|0||E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a {{convert|13|nmi|km|adj=on}} long tributary [[glacier]] in [[East Antarctica]]. It flows east from the [[Queen Alexandra Range]] to enter [[Beardmore Glacier]] at [[Sirohi Point]]. It was discovered by the [[British Antarctic Expedition, 1907–09]], under [[Ernest Shackleton]], and was named for the mother of [[Eric Marshall]], a member of Shackleton's South Polar Party.<ref name=gnis/>
