The most intense storm by lowest pressure and peak 10-minute sustained winds was [[Typhoon Tip]], which was also the most intense tropical cyclone ever recorded.

Storms with a minimum pressure of 900&nbsp;hPa (26.58&nbsp;inHg) or less are listed.  Storm information was less reliably documented and recorded before 1950.<ref name=":0" />

