==North Indian Ocean==
{{main|North Indian Ocean tropical cyclone}}

[[Image:Cyclone_05B.jpg|thumb| Satellite image of [[1999 Odisha cyclone|the cyclone]] as it made landfall in Odisha]]

The strongest tropical cyclone recorded in the North Indian Ocean is the [[1999 Odisha cyclone]], with 3-minute sustained winds of 260&nbsp;km/h (160&nbsp;mph) and a minimum pressure of {{convert|912|hPa|inHg|abbr=on|sigfig=4}}.

Storms with an intensity of {{convert|950|hPa|inHg|abbr=on|sigfig=4}} or less are listed.  Storm information was less reliably documented and recorded before 1971.<ref name=":0" />

