==South-West Indian Ocean==
{{main|South-West Indian Ocean tropical cyclone#Seasons}}
{{multiple image
 | width = 220
 | direction = vertical
 | image1 = Gafilo 2004-03-06 0655Z.jpg
 | caption1 = [[Cyclone Gafilo]] shortly before peak intensity
 | image2 = Fantala 2016-04-18 1025Z.jpg
 | caption2 = [[Cyclone Fantala]] shortly after peak intensity
}}
The most intense tropical cyclone in the South-West Indian Ocean is [[Cyclone Gafilo]]. By 10-minute sustained wind speed, the strongest tropical cyclone in the South-West Indian Ocean is [[Cyclone Fantala]].

Storms with an intensity of 920&nbsp;hPa (27.17&nbsp;inHg) or less are listed.  Storm information was less reliably documented and recorded before 1985.<ref name=":0" />

