==Australian region==
{{main|Australian region tropical cyclone#Seasons}}
{{multiple image
 | width = 220
 | direction = vertical
 | image1 = Inigo Apr 4 2003.png
 | caption1 = [[Cyclone Inigo]] near peak intensity
 | image2 = Marcus 2018-03-22 0632Z.jpg
 | caption2 = [[Cyclone Marcus]] at peak intensity
}}
The most intense tropical cyclones in the Australian Region are [[Cyclone Gwenda]] and [[Cyclone Inigo]]. By 10-minute sustained wind speed, the strongest are [[Cyclone Orson]] and [[Cyclone Monica]].

Storms with an intensity of 920&nbsp;hPa (27.17&nbsp;inHg) or less are listed. Storm information was less reliably documented and recorded before 1985.<ref name=":0" />
