==South Atlantic Ocean==
{{main|South Atlantic tropical cyclone}}
[[Image:Cyclone Catarina 2004.jpg|thumb|220px|[[Hurricane Catarina]] near peak intensity]]
Until recently, it was not known that tropical cyclones could exist in the southern Atlantic.  However, [[Hurricane Catarina]] in 2004, to date the only hurricane in the south Atlantic, brought additional review.  A subsequent study found that there was an average of 1-2 subtropical or tropical cyclones per year in the Southern Atlantic in recent decades.<ref>{{cite journal|author2=Braun, Aviva J|publisher=American Meteorological Society|year=2012|pages=7328–7340|title=A Climatology of Subtropical Cyclones in the South Atlantic|doi=10.1175/JCLI-D-11-00212.1|journal=Journal of Climate|volume=25|author1=Evans, Jenny L|bibcode=2012JCli...25.7328E}}</ref>
No official database of South Atlantic cyclones exists, but a partial list of tropical and subtropical systems with intensity below 1000&nbsp;hPa (29.53&nbsp;inHg) is listed.
